ased on the rule of law. They find that although ethical tension is inherent in the legal practice of all these societies, the legal profession is essential to stable political institutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aDondi, Angelo, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362440540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503624405423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503624405/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles